Compromise options (ranked for release day)

Option A — Log-triggered immediate emit + poll reschedule
Risk: lowest. Responsiveness gain: highest.

On activity-bearing log events (NewPrompt, PP progress, sampler_init, cached tokens, etc.):
1. try_emit immediately (fingerprint dedup still applies — no spam when unchanged)
2. Reschedule next_poll to poll_active_ms() (25ms)

• Extra HTTP: zero
• Extra IPC: only when meters actually change (same as before, just not delayed 2.5s)
• Crash exposure: negligible — this is the belt we built the whole system around

This alone likely fixes “1–5s before anything prints” for engines that log at all.

───

Option B — “Warm idle” tier (recently-used engine)
Risk: low–medium. Fixes quiet-stderr / /slots-only wake.

Add a third cadence based on last_slot_busy_at:

┌────────┬──────────────────────────────────┬───────────┬─────────────────────────┐
│ Tier   │ Condition                        │ Poll      │ Endpoints               │
├────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────┤
│ Active │ PP/TG / log_request_open         │ 25ms      │ /slots + /metrics       │
├────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────┤
│ Warm   │ idle but busy within last 30–60s │ 250–500ms │ /slots only             │
├────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────┤
│ Cold   │ no activity 60s+                 │ 2.5s      │ cheap /health heartbeat │
└────────┴──────────────────────────────────┴───────────┴─────────────────────────┘

During a coding session the engine stays in warm between turns — meters wake in <500ms even with zero stderr.

• 8 engines all coding: ~16–32 req/s (still below old 32 req/s, and no /metrics while warm)
• 8 engines truly idle overnight: stays ~3 req/s (unchanged)

