Option C — Constant tuning only (quick knob turn)
Risk: medium (blunt). Easy to ship in 10 minutes.

┌───────────────────────────────┬─────────┬───────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Knob                          │ Current │ Suggested │ Effect                                      │
├───────────────────────────────┼─────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ BLACKWELL_FUSION_IDLE_POLL_MS │ 2500    │ 1000      │ 2.5× faster cold wake                       │
├───────────────────────────────┼─────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ IDLE_CHEAP_HEALTH_STREAK_MAX  │ 2       │ 0         │ every idle tick hits /slots                 │
├───────────────────────────────┼─────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ INTER_REQUEST_GAP_HOLD_MS     │ 1200    │ 2000–3000 │ stay “in-flight” longer between agent reads │
└───────────────────────────────┴─────────┴───────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

8 cold idle engines at 1s /slots only ≈ 8 req/s — still ~4× below crash regime.

Downside: doesn’t fix the log→UI delay (Option A does). Less surgical.

───

Option D — Immediate /slots wake on emit_dirty
Risk: low. Middle ground between A and B.

When emit_dirty flips true and brain is idle-ready, fire one immediate /slots poll + emit before waiting for the timer. No change to steady-state idle cadence.

Catches Tom/quiet-stderr cases without permanently raising idle poll rate.

