My read

The throttling fix solved the right problem but accidentally created a wake latency cliff: stderr updates brain state immediately, UI waits on a 2.5s idle timer, and cheap /health ticks can skip /slots entirely.

That’s orthogonal to the engine rebuild — your full-day stability likely reflects both fixes (Wry workaround + engine), but meters responsiveness is purely our polling state machine now.

Option A is essentially free (no extra HTTP, minimal IPC risk) and should be non-negotiable for release. Option B or D handles the agent-session case where stderr is quiet.

